The paper deals with the semantics and evaluation of top-k queries in probabilistic databases, which is a topic that falls under the scope of database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of dynamic programming algorithms (cs.DS) and polynomial-time reductions (cs.CR) to solve the problem. Additionally, the paper discusses scoring functions and their injectivity, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG).
